{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 30 g of the olive oil, soy sauce, brown sugar, lemon zest from half the lemon and 25 g lemon juice into mixing bowl. Mix <b>20 sec\/speed 5<b>. Place salmon fillets in a deep dish and pour marinade from mixing bowl over the salmon. Place into refrigerator for 10 minutes and continue with recipe.","Place eschallots, garlic clove, leek, ginger and remaining 50 g olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 4<b>, then sauté <b>7 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, line Varoma tray with baking paper.","Add celery stalks, green peas, water and 1 tsp salt to mixing bowl. Set Varoma dish in position, add broccoli florets to it and season them with ½ tsp salt. Insert prepared Varoma tray, arrange salmon fillets on the tray, season with ½ tsp salt and ground black pepper and drizzle with marinade. Secure Varoma lid and cook <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep warm.","Add cream to mixing bowl, insert measuring cup and blend <b>2 min\/speed 5<b>-<strong>10, increasing speed gradually from speed 5 to speed 10.<\/strong> Serve soup for starter (see Tips), then salmon fillets and broccoli for main course."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g olive oil","50 g soy sauce","½ tsp brown sugar","1 lemon, zest and juice","4 skinless salmon fillets (150-180 g each)","100 g eschalots, cut into pieces","1 garlic clove","100 g leek, white part only, cut into pieces","20 - 30 g fresh ginger, peeled (optional)","100 g celery stalks, cut into pieces","350 g frozen green peas","450 g water","2 tsp salt","400 g broccoli","2 pinches ground black pepper","50 - 100 g pouring (whipping) cream, to taste"]}],"id":"r156149","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-RNjL7rDtmcQ\/XZQvSGAUPAI\/AAAAAAAAcb0\/wdz1UhQ9dEY3RPmNZky_AUOp0tBCVX4GwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_EYoNszxq6SuxGEk6.png","title":"Pea and ginger soup, lemon salmon with broccoli","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"pro